  "description": "Chisco-2.0 is an imagined speech electroencephalography (EEG) dataset comprising raw neurophysiological recordings from two participants (sub-01 and sub-02). The dataset contains EEG data in EDF format and represents a resource for investigating neural correlates of imagined speech production and related brain-computer interface applications. This dataset is derived from OpenNeuro ds006317.",
